// d4-raw-interp-attr.scrml — detector-validation fixture for D4 (S-RAW-INTERP).
//
// S202 acceptance bug 3 SHAPE: a `${...}` interpolation inside a string-literal
// markup attribute shipped as LITERAL TEXT into the rendered attribute value
// (href="/x/${load.id}" was JSON.stringify'd raw, surviving the `${` into the
// DOM). The current compiler LOWERS this correctly (the bug is fixed — see
// compiler/tests/browser/markup-value-render.browser.test.js), so a clean
// fixture no longer emits the literal `${`. The detector-validation test mounts
// this fixture (which renders clean today) and then reproduces the HISTORICAL
// broken render — a literal `${...}` surviving into an attribute value — to PROVE
// D4's attribute-value scan fires on the symptom. The fixture documents the shape.
<program>
<link>: string = "abc"
<main>
    <a href="/x/${ @link }">go</a>
</main>
</program>
